.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-ssl_checker \- Fetch TLS certificate metadata for any domain, calculate remaining validity days, run DNS record lookups, and probe for legacy TLS 1.0 and 1.1 support.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility ssl_checker
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Fetch TLS certificate metadata for any domain, calculate remaining validity days, run DNS record lookups, and probe for legacy TLS 1.0 and 1.1 support.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBCertificate inspection\fP — retrieves subject, issuer, and expiry date via \fCopenssl s_client\fP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBExpiry warning\fP — flags certificates expiring within 30 days and errors on already-expired ones
.IP \(bu 4
\fBDNS records\fP — looks up A, AAAA, MX, and TXT records using \fCdig\fP or \fCnslookup\fP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBLegacy TLS probe\fP — tests whether the server still accepts TLS 1.0 or TLS 1.1 connections
.IP \(bu 4
\fBCustom port support\fP — works on any port, not just 443
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments launches a guided prompt
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _ssl_checker/_ssl_checker.sh example.com

bash _ssl_checker/_ssl_checker.sh example.com --port 8443

bash _ssl_checker/_ssl_checker.sh example.com --no-dns

bash _ssl_checker/_ssl_checker.sh example.com --no-tls

bash _ssl_checker/_ssl_checker.sh example.com --no-dns --no-tls

bash _ssl_checker/_ssl_checker.sh
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fCHOST\fP   |   Domain or hostname to inspect
\fC--port N\fP   |   Port to connect on (default: \fC443\fP)
\fC--no-dns\fP   |   Skip DNS record lookups
\fC--no-tls\fP   |   Skip legacy TLS 1.0 and 1.1 probe
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OUTPUT SECTIONS
.PP
.SS Certificate details
.PP
.EX
  notBefore=Jan  1 00:00:00 2025 GMT
  notAfter=Jan  1 00:00:00 2026 GMT

Subject:  CN=example.com
Issuer :  C=US, O=Let's Encrypt, CN=R3
Days left: 194
.EE
.PP
The tool colors the days-left value green when healthy, yellow when under 30 days, and red when expired.
.PP
.SS DNS records
.PP
.EX
  DNS records for example.com
  ------------------------------------------------
  A       93.184.216.34
  AAAA    (no record)
  MX      0 .
  TXT     v=spf1 -all
.EE
.PP
.SS Legacy TLS probe
.PP
.EX
  ✔ TLS 1.0 rejected.
  ✔ TLS 1.1 rejected.
.EE
.PP
A warning is shown if either protocol is still accepted, since both are considered insecure.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fCopenssl\fP — required for certificate fetching and TLS probing
.IP \(bu 4
\fCdig\fP or \fCnslookup\fP — required for DNS lookups (skipped gracefully if neither is available)
.IP \(bu 4
\fCpython3\fP — used internally to calculate days remaining from the certificate expiry date
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH COMMON PORTS
.PP
Port   |   Use case
\fC443\fP   |   Standard HTTPS
\fC8443\fP   |   Alternate HTTPS
\fC465\fP   |   SMTPS (email)
\fC993\fP   |   IMAPS (email)
\fC5001\fP   |   Common local dev HTTPS
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   \fCopenssl\fP not installed, connection failed, or certificate already expired
